latestPosts.caption:
Save for later⬇️
1) VN (for reel edits)
My absolute favourite for editing reels. I usually edit directly in the IG app, but when I require detailed editing on phone, I go with VN only!
You can create 3 layer videos and videos with sliding clips on VN. The interface is quite beginner friendly. In-app ads are short & tolerable (the best part) and it’s watermark free.
2) ProCCD (for digital camera template)
Has filters with frames of digital cameras as template. Recreates the look of those vintage digital cameras. Not all the filters are free, but still it’s great!
3) Dazzcam (for retro filters)
This has the best looking retro filters I have seen, clean and realistic. It’s not available for android unfortunately.
4) Unfold (for fonts and templates)
Helps create the most visually pleasing and aesthetic stories with templates and fonts.
Maximum of my reel covers are from unfold.
5) Picsart (for hand drawn fonts)
This one lets you draw your own texts and use in reels. I also have the pro version with picsart.
The app is super useful for basic editing, cropping, texts inserting etc!
6) Prequel (unique filters)
Provides a lot of interesting filters that I haven’t found elsewhere. Most of their features are free!
7) LIGHTROOM (Photo editing)
This is the go-to free and easy photo editor that looks great. If I do have to edit a photo, Lightroom is my go-to app!
8) Captions (Al generated captions)
My last app I use to align my VO with my video.
Captions is the perfect app. Its super easy to use, has tons of features & use. It’s available only on iOS devices for around 4k annually.
Other apps I use are inShot, Snapseed, etc
Which are your go-to apps for photo & video editing ?
